{"name":"Nirahan the Starving","size":"large","type":"fiend","tag":"any race","alignment":"lawful evil","hitDice":"20","armorName":"natural armor","shieldBonus":0,"natArmorBonus":5,"otherArmorDesc":"18 (plate)","speed":"60","burrowSpeed":"50","climbSpeed":"0","flySpeed":"0","hover":false,"swimSpeed":"0","customHP":false,"customSpeed":false,"hpText":"97 (18d20 + 30)","speedDesc":"30 ft.","strPoints":"24","dexPoints":"12","conPoints":"22","intPoints":"12","wisPoints":"14","chaPoints":"18","blindsight":"0","blind":false,"darkvision":"0","tremorsense":"120","truesight":"0","telepathy":0,"cr":"13","customCr":"5 (1,800 XP)","customProf":3,"isLegendary":true,"legendariesDescription":"The Nirahan has three Villain Actions.","isLair":false,"lairDescription":"When fighting inside its lair, the black knight commander can invoke the ambient magic to take lair actions. On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the black knight commander can take one lair action to cause one of the following effects:","lairDescriptionEnd":"The black knight commander can't repeat an effect until they have all been used, and it can't use the same effect two rounds in a row.","isMythic":false,"mythicDescription":"If the black knight commander's mythic trait is active, it can use the options below as legendary actions for 1 hour after using {Some Ability}.","isRegional":false,"regionalDescription":"The region containing the black knight commander's lair is warped by the creature's presence, which creates one or more of the following effects:","regionalDescriptionEnd":"If the black knight commander dies, the first two effects fade over the course of 3d10 days.","properties":[],"abilities":[{"name":"Multiple Tongues","desc":"Nirahan has three tongues, each of which can be targeted with attacks (AC 20, immunity to psychic damage) while that tongue is grappling a creature. When a tongue takes 35 damage or more in a single turn, that tongue is destroyed, releasing the target. The worm can't use that tongue anymore. Damaging a tongue deals no damage to the worm."},{"name":"Slowed, Not Stopped (1 Soul)","desc":"When Nirahan fails a saving throw, they can choose to succeed instead. When they do, their speed and the reach of their tongue grab is reduced by a cumulative 10 feet until they finish a long rest."},{"name":"Tunneler","desc":"Nirahan can burrow through solid rock at half their burrowing speed and leaves a 10 foot diameter tunnel in their wake."}],"actions":[{"name":"Multiattack","desc":"Nirahan can make a number of tongue grab attacks equal to the number of tongues they currently have. Nirahan can replace any number of those attacks with a use of swallow"},{"name":"Tongue Grab","desc":"_Melee Weapon Attack:_ [STR ATK] to hit, reach 30 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [4D6] acid damage and the creature is grappled (escape DC 19). Until the grapple ends, the worm can't use this tongue against another target."},{"name":"Maw","desc":"_Melee Weapon Attack:_ [STR ATK] to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [STR 3D8] piercing damage. If the target is Huge or smaller, they must succeed on a DC 19 saving throw or be swallowed (as if by the swallow action)."},{"name":"Swallow","desc":"Nirahan pulls a huge or smaller grappled creature into their maw and swallows them. A swallowed creature is no longer grappled, but they are blinded and restrained, have total cover against attacks and other effects outside Nirahan, and take [8D6] acid damage at the start of each of the worm's turns.\n\nIf the worm takes 30 damage or more on a single turn from a creature inside them, the worm must succeed on a DC 21 constitution check at the end of that turn or regurgitate all swallowed creatures, each of whom fall prone in an unoccupied space within 10 feet of the worm."}],"bonusActions":[{"name":"Tongue Sweep","desc":"Nirahan violently swings a creature they have grappled. The grappled creature takes [3d6] bludgeoning damage, and each enemy within 10 feet of the grappled creature must succeed on a DC 16 Dexterity saving throw or take [3D6] bludgeoning damage."}],"reactions":[{"name":"Tongue Recall","desc":"When one of Nirahan's tongues takes damage that doesn't immediately destroy it, the worm can release any target that tongue is grappling and recall the tongue back inside the worm's body. That tongue can't be targeted until the worm uses it to grapple a creature again."}],"legendaries":[{"name":"Cannonball","desc":"Nirahan jumps and sends tremors through the ground and opening a 10 foot wide, 100 foot long, 20 foot deep fissure in the ground, originating from itself. Each creature in that area must make a DC 19 dexterity saving throw, taking [4D6] bludgeoning damage from the fall and landing prone. On a successful save, a creature flees to the closest unoccupied space outside the fissure's area."},{"name":"Earth Breach","desc":"Nirahan burrows up to half it's speed and then bursts through the surface, breaching the ground in a 10-foot-radius circle. Huge and smaller creatures within that area must succeed on a DC 19 Dexterity saving throw or be swallowed."},{"name":"Better Out than In","desc":"Nirahan projectile vomits the contents of their stomach in a 60-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a DC 19 dexterity saving throw, taking [6D6] acid damage on a failed save, or half as much on a sucessful one. Additionally, creatures who were swallowed by the worm are also regurgitated, taking [6D6] bludgeoning damage and landing prone."}],"mythics":[],"lairs":[],"regionals":[],"sthrows":[{"name":"con","order":2}],"skills":[],"damagetypes":[{"name":"acid","note":" (Resistant)","type":"r"},{"name":"fire","note":" (Resistant)","type":"r"}],"specialdamage":[],"conditions":[{"name":"charmed"},{"name":"frightened"}],"languages":[],"understandsBut":"","shortName":"","pluralName":"","doubleColumns":true,"separationPoint":6,"damage":[]}